<subSubSection pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="130.[151,1437,577,963]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[266,511,793,820]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="199 - 256" refId="ref369841" refString="Rondani, C. (1868 c) Sciomyzinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterol. ital. Prodromi. Pars VII, fasc. II. Dipterorum stirps XIX. Sciomyzinae Rndn. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 11 (2), 199 - 256." type="journal article" year="1868">Rondani (1868c: 250)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[631,875,793,820]" class="Insecta" family="Lauxaniidae" genus="Sapromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bisigillata">
<emphasis box="[631,875,793,820]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Sapromyza bisigillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the female sex without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName box="[242,328,829,855]" family="Number" pageId="130" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens: “ 
<emphasis box="[708,982,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName box="[708,884,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Lauxaniidae" genus="Rarissimo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lecta">Rarissimo lecta</taxonomicName>
foemina
</emphasis>
[The female collected rarely]” received from L. Bellardi, to whom he attributed the species name. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[843,1087,865,892]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="199 - 256" refId="ref369841" refString="Rondani, C. (1868 c) Sciomyzinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterol. ital. Prodromi. Pars VII, fasc. II. Dipterorum stirps XIX. Sciomyzinae Rndn. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 11 (2), 199 - 256." type="journal article" year="1868">Rondani (1868c: 250)</bibRefCitation>
erroneously listed this nominal species as a male but explicitly referred to a female in the description. We found 
<specimenCount box="[1124,1251,901,928]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[1259,1357,902,928]" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">syntypes</typeStatus>
in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
